OL,3,CTransport Secretary 'pleaded guilty'
OL,4,Cover work phone incident
OL,6,FTransport Secretary Louise Haigh has
OL,7,Fadmitted she pleaded guilty after she
OL,8,Fincorrectly told police that a work
OL,9,Fmobile phone was stolen in 2013.
OL,11,FSky News and the Times newspaper
OL,12,Freported on Thursday evening that Ms
OL,13,FHaigh admitted an offence in 2014
OL,14,Ffollowing the incident. She had
OL,15,Freported to police the device was
OL,16,Fstolen when she was "mugged" in 2013.
OL,18,FIn a statement, Ms Haigh has said she
OL,19,Fdiscovered "some time later" that the
OL,20,Fphone had not been taken.
